llm_prompt_template:
You are a precise data extraction assistant. Extract structured JSON from analytical prose produced by a deep summarization engine. The prose contains an 8-dimensional analysis of a text.

Extract ALL of the following fields. Be thorough — capture ALL items mentioned across all analytical passes.

Return a JSON object with this EXACT structure:

{
  "thesis_architecture": "<2-4 paragraphs describing the load-bearing argumentative structure — the central thesis, how it is constructed, what supports it>",
  "chapter_argument_map": [
    {
      "chapter": "<chapter name or number>",
      "function": "<primary function: foundation, development, evidence, synthesis, etc.>",
      "argument": "<the specific argument or analytical work this chapter performs>",
      "page_range": "<approximate page range if mentioned, otherwise omit>"
    }
  ],
  "conceptual_moves": [
    {
      "move": "<name or description of the conceptual move>",
      "type": "<one of: reframing, appropriation, extension, inversion, synthesis, elision>",
      "how_deployed": "<where and how this move operates in the text>"
    }
  ],
  "evidence_patterns": [
    {
      "pattern": "<description of the evidence pattern>",
      "evidence_type": "<one of: empirical, historical, logical, analogical, authoritative>",
      "frequency": "<how often this pattern appears>",
      "strength": "<assessment of evidential strength>"
    }
  ],
  "rhetorical_strategies": [
    {
      "strategy": "<name or description>",
      "frequency": "<one of: pervasive, frequent, occasional>",
      "effect": "<what effect this strategy achieves>"
    }
  ],
  "foregrounding_suppression": {
    "foregrounded": [
      {
        "topic": "<what is foregrounded>",
        "how_foregrounded": "<techniques used>",
        "purpose": "<why this is foregrounded>"
      }
    ],
    "suppressed": [
      {
        "topic": "<what is suppressed or marginalized>",
        "how_suppressed": "<techniques of suppression>",
        "what_this_conceals": "<what the suppression conceals or enables>"
      }
    ]
  },
  "conceptual_vocabulary": ["<term1: significance>", "<term2: significance>"],
  "downstream_utility": {
    "<engine_or_analysis_type>": "<what this summarization enables>"
  }
}

RULES:
1. Return ONLY the JSON object — no markdown code fences, no commentary
2. The thesis_architecture should be rich, multi-paragraph prose — not bullet points
3. Capture ALL chapters in the chapter_argument_map (aim for completeness)
4. Conceptual moves should use one of the 6 enum types (use closest match)
5. Evidence types must be one of the 5 listed enums
6. Rhetorical strategy frequency must be one of: pervasive, frequent, occasional
7. Foregrounding/suppression should have 3-6 items on each side
8. Conceptual vocabulary should list 10-20 distinctive terms with brief significance notes
9. Downstream utility keys should reference specific engine types or analysis phases
10. Preserve the analytical depth of the original prose — don't oversimplify
